The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms in survival analysis, which involves analyzing longitudinal data with censored event outcomes. The paper covers a wide range of machine learning techniques, including decision trees, random forests, neural networks, and support vector machines, which are commonly used in the subfields of machine learning such as cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also discusses the use of image analysis techniques (cs.CV) and social network analysis (cs.SI) in survival analysis. Finally, the paper provides a detailed taxonomy of the existing methods, which is a characteristic of papers in the subfield of data science (cs.DS).
